==German==

===Noun===
{{PAGENAME}} {{m}}

#{{geometry}} A surface created by projecting a closed two-dimensional curve along an axis perpendicular to the plane of the curve.
#:When the two-dimensional curve is a circle, the cylinder is a ''[[Kreiszylinder]]''. In non-mathematical usage, ''Zylinder'' is a de-facto synonyme to ''[[Kreiszylinder]]''.
#{{geometry}} A solid figure bounded by a cylinder and two parallel planes intersecting the cylinder.
#Any object in the form of a circular cylinder. [[Image:Cylinder.png|Drawing of a cylinder (2)]]
#A [[cylindrical]] cavity or chamber in a mechanism, mostly the counterpart to a piston found in a piston-driven engine.
#A container in the form of a cylinder, as used e.g. in a pneumatic dispatch system (in speech usually replaced by more specific/colloquial terms, not so in formal writing)
#An early form of phonograph recording, made on a wax cylinder (hardly used term)
#A cylinder hat.

